2 HOUSE BILL 921
1 9–1110.
2 (A) THIS SECTION APPLIES TO ALL EMPLOYEES, INCLUDING TEMPORARY
3 EMPLOYEES, IN THE EXECUTIVE, JUDICIAL, AND LEGISLATIVE BRANCHES OF
4 STATE GOVERNMENT, INCLUDING ANY UNIT WITH AN INDEPENDENT PERSONNEL
5 SYSTEM.
6 (B) AN EMPLOYEE SUBJECT TO THIS SECTION IS ENTITLED TO COLLEAGUE
7 BEREAVEMENT LEAVE WITH PAY.
8 (C) (1) SUBJECT TO PARAGRAPH (2) OF THIS SUBSECTION, AN EMPLOYEE
9 MAY USE UP TO 5 DAYS OF COLLEAGUE BEREAVEMENT LEAVE IMMEDIATELY
10 FOLLOWING THE DEATH OF A COLLEAGUE WHO IS EMPLOYED BY THE SAME AGENCY
11 AS THE EMPLOYEE IF:
12 (I) THE COLLEAGUE’S DEATH OCCURS ON THE JOB; AND
13 (II) THE EMPLOYEE WORKS IN CLOSE PROXIMITY TO THE
14 COLLEAGUE WHO DIED.
15 (2) AN EMPLOYEE MAY USE COLLEAGUE BEREAVEMENT LEAVE ONLY
16 AFTER NOTIFYING THE EMPLOYEE’S APPOINTING AUTHORITY OF THE EMPLOYEE’S
17 INTENTION TO USE COLLEAGUE BEREAVEMENT LEAVE.
18 (3) AN EMPLOYEE’S APPOINTING AUTHORITY MAY NOT REQUIRE AN
19 EMPLOYEE ENTITLED TO USE COLLEAGUE BEREAVEMENT LEAVE UNDER
20 PARAGRAPH (1) OF THIS SUBSECTION TO USE ANY OTHER PAID LEAVE AVAILABLE
21 TO THE EMPLOYEE.
22 (D) THE SECRETARY SHALL ADOPT REGULATIONS GOVERNING COLLEAGUE
23 BEREAVEMENT LEAVE.
24 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
25 October 1, 2025.

